Dakota’s Finn Forrest CGC ✨

insanely proud of this little man. we put off the CGC test for awhile due to being busy with life, but we are so happy to finally gain the title. 

In July 2022, Finn received his S.T.A.R. Puppy title and the next step was to continue on to CGC. with the time in between, Finn easily could’ve let go of all that training and picked up bad habits, but he didn’t because 1) he’s smart & 2) we never stopped the training as owners.

so seriously, never stop working with your dog. it keeps them engaged & well behaved, but more importantly, it continues to grow the bond between you & your furry friend.

Big thanks to our local training facility on all they do & continue to do for Finn. 🫶🏼💙💛 pawspetresortsd

2 years ago,  this little guy got out from the shelter and made me the happiest person. 
Now, he is my forever buddy. 
We have learned how to communicate each other through a lot of training. 
We just accomplished the first of many goals we have as a team. We passed the “Canine Good Citizen” test from AKC.

We adopted Arya at 6 months old. She was very sweet but super energetic and a little crazy due to spending her early days on the street. We knew immediately that we had our work cut out for us. When we started training with LARPO, passing the CGC test seemed like something in the very far future, but we were determined to get there - not only for her/our benefit but for the benefit of her breed. Breaking down those stereotypes was key! I’m so proud of how far she has come and can’t wait to see her continue to become the best dog ever!  ~ Amanda, Arya’s mom

💬 What is the CGC?

Also known as the Canine Good Citizen 🐕 

The CGC is a program developed by the American Kennel Club (AKC) to recognize and reward "responsible pet ownership for owners and basic good manners for dogs." In addition to receiving a from the AKC, the dog is automatically recorded in the AKC's Canine Good Citizen archive.

So double tap and comment congratulations to Cowboy and his loving owner Lucas! 👏🏼

Guess who passed her Canine Good Citizen test! 🥳

Lexi is now “Lexi Rose CGC”

I haven't been active on here lately and that's mainly because the dogs and I have been going through training and I just wanted to focus on them during it.

Training for this was such a fun experience. I got to learn so much about what to do and how to communicate better with the dogs. 

During the test, I was so nervous that Lexi was going to pick up on my anxiety and react but she thankfully pulled through with only one hiccup. 

For our sit and lay down/stay in place, you can see in the video I had trouble getting Lexi to focus on me and listen to what I'm saying. I was extremely frustrated cause I know she can do it but I had to remind myself that being frustrated wasn't going to help her. So I had to readjust and after the second try, she did it.

I'm super excited to see what's in store for us next. Our trainer recommends we try Rally, Scent work, and Temperament test so I might sign her up for one of those.

insanely proud of this little man. we put off the CGC test for awhile due to being busy with life, but we are so happy to finally gain the title. 

In July 2022, Finn received his S.T.A.R. Puppy title and the next step was to continue on to CGC. with the time in between, Finn easily could’ve let go of all that training and picked up bad habits, but he didn’t because 1) he’s smart & 2) we never stopped the training as owners.

so seriously, never stop working with your dog. it keeps them engaged & well behaved, but more importantly, it continues to grow the bond between you & your furry friend.

💬 What is the CGC?

Also known as the Canine Good Citizen 🐕 

The CGC is a program developed by the American Kennel Club (AKC) to recognize and reward "responsible pet ownership for owners and basic good manners for dogs." In addition to receiving a from the AKC, the dog is automatically recorded in the AKC's Canine Good Citizen archive.

Guess who passed her Canine Good Citizen test! 🥳

Lexi is now “Lexi Rose CGC”

I haven't been active on here lately and that's mainly because the dogs and I have been going through training and I just wanted to focus on them during it.

Training for this was such a fun experience. I got to learn so much about what to do and how to communicate better with the dogs. 

During the test, I was so nervous that Lexi was going to pick up on my anxiety and react but she thankfully pulled through with only one hiccup. 

For our sit and lay down/stay in place, you can see in the video I had trouble getting Lexi to focus on me and listen to what I'm saying. I was extremely frustrated cause I know she can do it but I had to remind myself that being frustrated wasn't going to help her. So I had to readjust and after the second try, she did it.

I'm super excited to see what's in store for us next. Our trainer recommends we try Rally, Scent work, and Temperament test so I might sign her up for one of those. 

Check out shop

You’re looking at one of the newest CGC title holders in the americankennelclub 😅 Was our test perfectly executed? No. It’s a real game-changer when you don’t have treats to shape behaviors! But I am still very proud of how far we have come. Plenty of work to do, but a great start to earning many more AKC titles 😏
